FBIS4-59799 "drnes096_q_94001" FBIS-NES-94-096 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Bangladesh Visit of Burmese Trade Minister Reported Visit of Burmese Trade Minister Reported Arrives To Sign Trade Accord BK1405162394 Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network in English 1530 GMT 14 May 94 BK1405162394 Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network English BFN [Text] Trade between Bangladesh and Myanmar [Burma] will start soon after signing the border trade agreement between the two countries. The visiting Myanmar minister for trade, Lieutenant General Tun Kyi, said this on his arrival in Dhaka today from Chittagong. Talking to newsmen, he said the agreement will be signed on Wednesday. The Myanmar trade minister and his Bangladesh counterpart, Shamsul Islam, will sign it. The Myanmar minister said border trade can help (?accelerate) the development of the regions of the two countries across their borders. Replying to a question, Mr. Kyi said his government welcomed the Myanmar refugees back home.
